# Frontend Rules — Admin Service

## Stack (No Build Step)

- **Jinja2** templates rendered server-side by FastAPI.
- **htmx** from CDN — pin to a specific version tag, never `@latest`:
  ```html
  <script src="https://unpkg.com/htmx.org@2.0.3" integrity="sha384-…" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  ```
- **Tailwind CSS** via CDN Play CDN in development; pin version in production.
- **Chart.js** for data visualisation — loaded from CDN, initialised in `static/js/charts.js`.
- **No TypeScript, no React, no Vue, no bundler, no npm.**

## htmx Attribute Patterns

Every interactive element uses `hx-*` attributes — no raw `fetch()`, no inline `onclick`.

### Basic mutation
```html
<button
  hx-post="/admin/orders/{{ order.id }}/approve"
  hx-target="#order-row-{{ order.id }}"
  hx-swap="outerHTML"
  hx-indicator="#spinner-{{ order.id }}">
  Approve
</button>
<span id="spinner-{{ order.id }}" class="htmx-indicator">⏳</span>
```

### Polling (live data)
```html
<div hx-get="/admin/status/feeds"
     hx-trigger="every 5s"
     hx-swap="innerHTML"
     id="feed-status">
  {% include "components/_feed_status.html" %}
</div>
```

### Infinite scroll / pagination
```html
<tr hx-get="/admin/orders?page={{ next_page }}"
    hx-trigger="revealed"
    hx-swap="afterend">
  <td colspan="6">Loading…</td>
</tr>
```

### Boost internal navigation
```html
<a href="/admin/orders" hx-boost="true">Orders</a>
```

## Confirmation Modals

A confirmation modal is **required** before completing any of these actions:

| Trigger | Modal must display |
|---------|--------------------|
| Any SQL write (INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE) via admin UI | Table name, operation, affected row count |
| `tb restart <svc>` call | Service name + current health status |
| Order approve / reject | Order ID, side, quantity, instrument, current status |
| Proposal approve / reject | Proposal ID, submitter, one-line description |

Implementation pattern using the shared `_confirm_modal.html` partial:

```html
<!-- Simple: hx-confirm for non-critical actions -->
<button hx-delete="/admin/cache/{{ key }}"
        hx-confirm="Delete cache key '{{ key }}'? This cannot be undone.">
  Delete
</button>

<!-- Complex: modal partial for high-stakes actions -->
<button
  hx-get="/admin/orders/{{ order.id }}/confirm-approve"
  hx-target="#modal-container"
  hx-swap="innerHTML">
  Approve
</button>
```

## Chart.js Patterns

```javascript
// static/js/charts.js
// Charts are initialised from data attributes — no inline <script> tags in templates.

document.querySelectorAll('[data-chart]').forEach(el => {
  const type = el.dataset.chart;            // "line" | "bar" | "doughnut"
  const data = JSON.parse(el.dataset.chartData);
  new Chart(el, { type, data, options: defaultOptions(type) });
});
```

```html
<!-- Template: pass data via data attribute, never inline <script> -->
<canvas
  data-chart="line"
  data-chart-data="{{ chart_data | tojson }}"
  class="w-full h-64">
</canvas>
```

- No inline `<script>` blocks in templates — all JS lives in `static/js/`.
- Chart data injected via `data-*` attributes and parsed in `charts.js`.
- Use `| tojson` Jinja2 filter (not `| safe` — avoids XSS).

## Tailwind Utility Conventions

- Use Tailwind utility classes directly in HTML — no custom CSS files unless unavoidable.
- Consistent component classes extracted to a Jinja2 macro:
  ```html
  {# templates/macros/ui.html #}
  {% macro btn_primary(text, **attrs) %}
  <button class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700 disabled:opacity-50"
          {{ attrs | xmlattr }}>{{ text }}</button>
  {% endmacro %}
  ```
- Dark mode via `dark:` variants — keep consistent with `class="dark"` on `<html>`.
- No `style=""` inline attributes — use Tailwind arbitrary values `[...]` if needed.

## Security

- Never render user-supplied strings with `{{ var | safe }}` — always use `{{ var }}`.
- All mutating forms must include the CSRF token:
  ```html
  <input type="hidden" name="csrf_token" value="{{ csrf_token }}">
  ```
- No secrets, API keys, or internal IDs exposed in HTML source or `data-*` attributes.
- CSP header set by the FastAPI middleware — do not add `unsafe-inline` script sources.

## Template Structure

```
services/admin_service/templates/
├── base.html                 # Layout shell, CDN script tags, modal container
├── _confirm_modal.html       # Reusable confirmation modal (htmx-powered)
├── _flash.html               # Flash / toast message partial
├── macros/
│   └── ui.html               # Button, badge, table-row macros
├── components/               # Reusable htmx fragment partials
│   ├── _feed_status.html
│   ├── _order_row.html
│   └── _proposal_card.html
└── pages/                    # Full-page templates (one per route group)
    ├── dashboard.html
    ├── orders.html
    └── proposals.html
```
